<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="384" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="4.[167,1376,2924,3469]" pageId="4" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,521,3279,3312]" pageId="4" pageNumber="384">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. Small global distribution of the Javan Slitfaced Bat and its dependence on lowland rainforest make it of particular conservation concern. It is currently the most threatened species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van der Hoeven" authorityYear="1855" box="[169,323,3397,3430]" class="Mammalia" family="Nycteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Nycteridae</taxonomicName>
. Practically nothing is known about its ecology, impeding implementation of effective conservation action.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
